07/08/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Russian Ambassador to Serbia Alexander Konuzin says his government may provide a credit of $1 billion in budget support to Serbia. Speaking on Thursday (August 6th) about an October visit by Russian President Dmitry Medvedev, Konuzin said Moscow has already approved the possibility of providing financial support to Belgrade. Russia, he said, expects to strengthen its partnership with Serbia, mostly in the energy sector. Medvedev will be the first Russian president to visit since 2001. (Tanjug, B92, Danas, Vesti - 06/08/09)
